HEADWORD: Pseudoscopic
<hw>Pseu`do*scop"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Opt.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or formed by, a pseudoscope; having its parts
appearing with the relief reversed; <as>as, a <ex>pseudoscopic</ex>
image</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

